3. Validation Checklist
3.1 Completeness

✅ All identified stakeholder requirements addressed
✅ Success criteria defined for each requirement
✅ Acceptance criteria measurable and testable
✅ Dependencies between requirements documented
✅ Traceability established (Requirements → Use Cases → Design)

3.2 Consistency

✅ No conflicting requirements identified
✅ Terminology consistent across all documents (validated against glossary)
✅ Requirements aligned with project scope and objectives
✅ Priorities consistent with business and operational value

3.3 Clarity

✅ Requirements written in clear and unambiguous language
✅ Technical terminology defined in glossary
✅ Each requirement addresses a single, testable concern
✅ Acceptance criteria specific and verifiable

3.4 Feasibility

✅ Requirements achievable within allocated budget
✅ Requirements achievable within defined project timeline
✅ Selected technology stack supports all requirements
✅ Team skills sufficient or supported by training plans

4. Open Issues and Risks
4.1 Open Issues
Issue ID	Description	Impact	Resolution Plan	Owner
ISSUE-001	Selection of final predictive algorithm	Medium	Evaluate models during initial development sprint	Data Science Lead
ISSUE-002	Cloud deployment decision pending	Medium	Finalize hosting platform before deployment phase	Project Manager
ISSUE-003	Report export formats finalization	Low	Confirm formats during testing phase	Product Owner
4.2 Risks
Risk ID	Description	Probability	Impact	Mitigation
RISK-001	Prediction accuracy below expected threshold	Medium	High	Iterative model tuning and validation
RISK-002	Data quality issues in historical sales data	Medium	Medium	Data preprocessing and validation rules
RISK-003	Performance degradation with data growth	Low	Medium	Load testing and scalable architecture
5. Assumptions and Constraints Acknowledgment
5.1 Acknowledged Assumptions

All stakeholders acknowledge the following assumptions documented in the SRS:

✅ Availability of historical sales and inventory data
✅ Users have basic inventory management knowledge
✅ Stable internet connectivity for web access
✅ English language support sufficient for Phase 1
✅ Inventory updates performed regularly

5.2 Acknowledged Constraints

All stakeholders acknowledge the following constraints:

✅ Fixed project budget as approved by institution/organization
✅ Defined academic/project submission timeline
✅ Web-based architecture using approved technology stack
✅ Initial support for limited concurrent users
✅ Compliance with data security and privacy guidelines

6. Change Management Agreement
6.1 Baseline Establishment

By signing this document, stakeholders agree that the requirements defined in Version 1.0 represent the official baseline for the Predictive Stock Management System.

6.2 Change Control Process

Any future changes to requirements shall follow the process below:

Change Request Submission: Formal request submitted with justification

Impact Analysis: Assessment of impact on scope, schedule, and effort

Review & Prioritization: Evaluation by Project Guide and Project Manager

Approval Decision:

Minor changes: Project Guide approval

Major changes: Institutional/Project Review Committee approval

Documentation Update: Version increment and revision history update

Communication: Notify all stakeholders

